{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Petition privacy notice · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}What the OIATC "Add your voice" petition system collects, where it is stored, how long it is kept, and how to have your signature removed.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-petition-privacy{% endblock %}
{% block topnav %}<a href="/">&larr; Home</a>{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
  <style>
    .pet-priv { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--gap-7) var(--gap-5) var(--gap-9); }
    .pet-priv h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(28px, 4.2vw, 38px); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 var(--gap-3); }
    .pet-priv h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.25; margin: var(--gap-6) 0 var(--gap-3); }
    .pet-priv p, .pet-priv li { color: var(--ink-2); }
    .pet-priv p { margin: 0 0 var(--gap-3); }
    .pet-priv strong { color: var(--ink); }
    .pet-priv ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin: 0 0 var(--gap-4); }
    .pet-priv li { position: relative; padding-left: 20px; margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.6; }
    .pet-priv li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 3px; top: 12px; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent); }
    .pet-priv a { color: var(--accent-deep); }
    .pet-priv .note { background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 18px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink-2); line-height: 1.6; margin: var(--gap-5) 0; }
    .pet-priv .byline { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink-3); margin: var(--gap-6) 0 0; padding-top: var(--gap-4); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="pet-priv">
  <p class="eyebrow">OIATC · Petition privacy notice</p>
  <h1>How your information is handled</h1>
  <p>When you add your voice to a petition on this site, here is exactly what happens to your information. This is written plainly and built around the First Nations principles of <strong>OCAP</strong> (Ownership, Control, Access, Possession).</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Your name</strong> and <strong>email address</strong>.</li>
    <li>Whether you told us you are a <strong>Sagamok member or a supporter</strong> (self-declared; we do not check, and we never ask for proof).</li>
    <li>An optional <strong>comment</strong>, if you write one.</li>
    <li>Your choice of <strong>whether your name may be shown publicly</strong> later.</li>
    <li>A one-way, scrambled fingerprint of your network address and browser, used <strong>only</strong> to stop automated abuse. It cannot be turned back into your address and is never shown to anyone.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We <strong>never</strong> collect your band registry number, date of birth, or any government identifier. We never add advertising or analytics trackers to this form.</p>

  <h2>Where it is stored</h2>
  <p>Your signature is stored in <strong>OIATC's own database, on infrastructure OIATC controls in Canada</strong>. It is not sent to Mailchimp, Google, a US petition platform, or any other third-party service. (One technical note in the spirit of full honesty: like most of the site, traffic reaches our server through a content-delivery network, so your submission passes through that network in transit before it is stored on our own servers.)</p>

  <h2>How it is used</h2>
  <p>Signatures are counted and, when a campaign is ready, the list of supporters is presented to the named recipient (for example, Sagamok Chief and Council). Your email is used to identify your signature and to let you remove it; we do not sell, rent, or share it, and there is no marketing list.</p>

  <h2>How long it is kept</h2>
  <p>Your signature is kept while the campaign is active and for a reasonable period afterward so the result can be presented and verified. When it is no longer needed, signature data for a closed campaign is deleted.</p>

  <h2>How to remove yours</h2>
  <p>You can remove your signature at any time using the personal remove link shown to you right after you sign. If you no longer have it, write to <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a> and we will remove it for you.</p>

  <div class="note"><strong>Please note:</strong> this notice is general information, not legal advice. It is a draft pending review.</div>

  <p class="byline">A community resource from OIATC, the Ontario Indigenous AI &amp; Technology Council. Questions or corrections: <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a>.</p>
</article>
{% endblock %}
